OL,3,CWorld-first gene-editing therapy for
OL,4,Cblood disorders approved for NHS use
OL,6,FSold as Casgevy, the treatment has
OL,7,Fbeen recommended by NICE to treat
OL,8,Fpatients aged 12 and over the
OL,9,Ftransfusion-dependent beta thalassemia
OL,10,F(TDT) which can lead to severe anaemia.
OL,12,FAccording to the NHS, around 17,000
OL,13,Fpeople live with the disease, with 250
OL,14,Fnew cases each year. It is more common
OL,15,Fin people of Black African, Caribbean,
OL,16,FMiddle Eastern and South Asian
OL,17,Fheritage.
OL,19,FThose who suffer from the inherited
OL,20,Fcondition rely on regular lifelong
OL,21,Fblood transfusions to survive.
