OL,3,CWorld-first gene-editing therapy for
OL,4,Cblood disorders approved for NHS use
OL,6,FThe only curative treatment currently
OL,7,Favailable for people with sickle cell
OL,8,Fin the UK is a donor stem cell
OL,9,Ftransplant, so Casgevy is an option
OL,10,Ffor patients when a stem cell
OL,11,Ftransplant is suitable but no donor
OL,12,Fcan be found.
OL,14,FCasgevy works by modifying the faulty
OL,15,Fgene in a patient's bone marrow stem
OL,16,Fcells so the body produces functioning
OL,17,Fhaemoglobin - the protein found in red
OL,18,Fblood cells that carries oxygen in
OL,19,Fyour body and gives blood its red
OL,20,Fcolour. The edited cells are then
OL,21,Finfused back into the patient.
